The paper discusses deep clustering algorithms that combine representation learning with deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on image and time-series datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of autoencoders and manifold learning methods also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on clustering and discovering clusters suggests information theory (cs.IT) as a possible sub-category, although this is less likely than the others.
